Text.Value: Yes. Although it may be a touch cold by now.
*It feels ten times its size. Alive, awake. Almost smug.*
No, I want this power. Keep your ring.
Refresh my memory - what do you need for the potion?
In the beginning, I had an arrangement with a lich. Excellent company, despite what one would expect.
But unless you are already a step from death, it will not kill you.
Of course. Return when you are ready.
Leave.
You were supposed to make it weaker, not stronger!
What's next? Cutting off my own head?
*Omeluum watches you with cautious intensity. It expects doubt. It expects fear.*
I cannot change my appetites. Although I am experimenting in reducing them with magic.
Perhaps the peoples of the Underdark will be less inclined to violence if they comprehend the cost, yes?
I suppose it's not all bad. More power is better than less.
Drown out the tadpole by focusing on a tune.
Drink the potion.
Extracting the larva would kill you. Immediately.
YOUR LIFE. GIVE IT.
Something of little value - your life.
Because removal seemed preferable to negation.
*The world loses its edges, its finer boundaries. You are fluid but trapped, like a creature suspended in amber.*
I intend no disrespect, but one can only heal so much of their own brain tissue.
Understandable. If you change your mind in the future, say as such. I will perform the experiment then.
But not to worry. Should you transform, I will happily perform a new examination.
Wall off your mind from the psionic seizure.
That is not a story I share with strangers.
I do not intend to shatter its protection.
I felt it grow inside me. There's more power than ever.
Tell Omeluum about the strange mind flayer ship you were on.
That's too risky of an experiment for me. Count me out.
I greet you, child of the stars. How has your search for the mushrooms fared?
I greet you, child of the dark. How has your search for the mushrooms fared?
I greet you, child of the sun. How has your search for the mushrooms fared?
I want that ring to protect my mind.
If you require it on another occasion, merely ask.
How disappointing.
I enslaved no one, and stand against such practice. I cannot surrender my own shield for nothing.
That's disgusting. You're a monster.
Indeed. Although I may have another solution, albeit a temporary one.
Only in that you may be a danger to yourself. What the potion may make you see or feel - I cannot determine.
The larva is not the only creature that has been inside this brain. But at present it is the sole resident.
Is this enough gold for it?
Don't waste my time. Say what you mean.
*A few sparks and colours dance around Omeluum, but you stay steady and staring ahead.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Small colorful FX on the screen.

Text.Value: Eating those doesn't sound like a great idea.
A fascinating topic indeed. What can you tell me?
I was born with a propensity for arcane magic my people despise. It gave me the strength to resist the elder brain.
Perform the tale of your adventures so far: 'The Ballad of Brains, Brine Pools and Balderdash.'
Nice. Helps not to judge a book by its cover, doesn't it.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Reaction on player acquiring the ring. Might be from persuasion or from buying it from Omeluum.

Text.Value: Relax and allow Omeluum's mind to search yours.
I think I already have what you're looking for.
I wouldn't be in this situation if it wasn't for a mind flayer. You owe me.
What exactly is this going to do to me?
There may be a way to bypass that stasis. There are many alchemical substances that can influence the mind.
To deal with this abomination? Nigh unthinkable. Yet even Vlaakith herself could not deny the ring's merit.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Reaction on player acquiring the ring. Might be from persuasion or from buying it from Omeluum.

Text.Value: No, I'm done with all this.
A tongue of madness and the spores from a timmask mushroom.
Take a look at those mushrooms yet?

EditorData.logicalname: Question (fallback when gave mushrooms but dialog ended)

Text.Value: But I have... an idea.
Hm. I am afraid you have not offered any information I do not already possess.
Of course, the larva remains. Be ever-vigilant of its growth.
Call to your god for protection.
So I left his company, and thus I now feed from those who... act against the Society's goals.
My mind is all addled, can you tell why?
Such crude destruction may not waylay a larva like this. But there is another possibility.
I need only bypass the interference that prevents me from communicating with the larva.
My formula will hamper the more harmful effects once the mushrooms are brewed into a potion.
This is most unusual. The incubation period should be complete, as should your transformation.
Except... it does not seem to be on my person. Did I leave it on that last expedition somewhere? Hm.
But the larva is infused with strange magic. It appears to be in some form of stasis.
Give a dramatic retelling of your time on the mind flayer ship.
I would require a fresh tongue of madness and timmask spores.
It seems as if someone did not want you to.
These are fine specimens. It will only take me a moment to brew them to proper potency.
Lovely. So where do I find these mushrooms?
How about I tell you more about that nautiloid? Every last detail.
Of course. I am sorry I cannot assist you in its removal.
My apologies. I cannot trade what I do not possess.
Leave.
Offer a detailed, logical analysis of the nautiloid.
Die, abomination! Attack.
There's no trusting a mind flayer. Attack.
My research is in perpetual need of funding. Yes, I am willing to accept your coin.
Your people enslaved mine. The debt is yours to repay.
Do you still have that potion? I'm ready.
Ahem. Death. It means you would have to die first to extract the tadpole.
Never mind. I'm done with mind flayers touching me.
Oh? Perhaps I should start taking notes.
*As Omeluum's mind pierces yours, the tadpole pulses with power.*
I understand the potion has put you in a... precarious condition. But I will not respond to such threats.
I never thought we'd bargain with an illithid. Let's hope this ring proves invaluable.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Reaction on player acquiring the ring. Might be from persuasion or from buying it from Omeluum.

Text.Value: You must drink the entire draught. I can make no promises as to its taste.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Omeluum turns to face the player, offering them a potion bottle.

Text.Value: A nautiloid? Fascinating. I have never set foot on one myself.
I greet you, friend of the dark.
Such an outcome was not in my calculations. There is more to this being than mere stasis.
Every waking hour, I pushed back against its dire hold. My wizardry empowered me.
Greetings. What knowledge do you seek?
I have gold. Will that suit?
We shouldn't cause trouble, Omeluum. There are enough threats down here in the Underdark.
*The parasite swells with power - more power than you have ever felt before.*
I need some time to prepare.
It is not ideal. The process would surely kill you.
Are you so keen to know my pain, young gith?
What happens if that stasis goes away?
I offered her the chance to join the Society, but she refused. Her experiments on sussur bark took priority.
Leave.
It will not remove the larva, but it will limit its influence, both positive and negative.
Bashing my skull is just part of a day's work.
I greet you, child of the stars.
Why didn't you mention the ring before this potion debacle?
*The tadpole spasms, seizes. It's fighting the potion even harder than you are.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player grabs their head in agony, tadpole halo FX/effect in place.

Text.Value: But our ambitions eventually splintered. I wished to better the world, and he preferred its rot.
What aren't you telling me? Is this experiment dangerous?
You have my deepest apologies. The larva did not care for my intentions.
*The potion is disgusting beyond description. The only mercy is that it goes down quickly.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Character winces and flinches in disgust.

Text.Value: I required brains, he required souls. A perfect symbiosis.
The Underdark, of course. Although they are quite rare, and their discovery... perilous.
*You're sinking - sinking into a starless void that has no end. The connection between mind and body draws thin and tight.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Character's eyes go wide, staring off into nothing.

Text.Value: I possess a Ring of Mind-Shielding. It prevents elder brains from noticing my presence.
No fear. ONLY FURY!
Fear? What's that?
*An almost childlike joy enters Omeluum's ichor-laced eyes.*
Omeluum! Are you well?
Oh Gods, what do you mean?
Not a drop left. Very good.
Here. I made a potion of those mushrooms. Will this work?
Bypass? What kind of alchemy are we talking about?
Perhaps with time, it can be one brain a year instead of one a month...
*Dark holes bite at the edges of your vision, but the void cannot draw you in.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Darkness FX pushes in from the edge of the screen.

Text.Value: Let me see your wares.
That larva is like nothing I have ever observed before. Its power is... unsettling.
Either give me the ring, or I'll run you through.
Let the terror take you.
Leave.
I found those mushrooms you were looking for.
Thanks for the information.
The moment its control shattered, I fled before the colony discovered I had defected.
I see. I will remain here if you decide otherwise.
Best way to deal with that sort of hunger, I suppose.
That doesn't sound ideal.
You may find them in nature, or the nearby cleric's tower. Be cautious - those that have taken root are quite dangerous.
But be warned. In their natural state, both of these mushrooms can be quite dangerous.
You return. Have you changed your mind about the ring?
She is quite fond of her garden. Lenore has always been a lonely sort - nature was her only companion.
All right. I'll come back when I find the mushrooms.
My apologies. I hope the experience was not too unpleasant.
*As Omeluum watches your performance, something stirs in his mind, unusual for an illithid: joy.*
As the potion influences your mind, you may find yourself acting irrationally. Try and stay focused.
I would offer it as a gift, but in truth, the ring is priceless. Is there anything you could offer me in turn?
*The cold blades lose their edge. You are stalwart, turning that tide of fear against itself.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [REUSE] SCENE_CRA_Mindmeld_Pain_PLYR_OUT if the player succeeds their check
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player relaxes. Tadpole halo/FX in place.

Text.Value: Your sanity, however much you possess, should remain intact.
It holds far more power than it should. For the larva to react to my manipulations in such a way is beyond my ken.
A bold strategy. It is not many that can defeat their own minds.
They were our warships during the greatest eras of the Illithid Empire. We ruled the entire Astral Plane from their decks.
That thing better work. If it doesn't, I doubt you'll be in any position to complain...

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Reaction on player acquiring the ring. Might be from persuasion or from buying it from Omeluum.
EditorData.NodeContext: 'I hope that was a good bargain you just made' - player just acquired a ring with magical properties.

Text.Value: *A wave of psychic force batters your mind, cruel and calculating. You are nothing to it. You are small.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player buckles in pain. Tadpole halo FX/effect.

Text.Value: Stare into the swirling abyss.
I assumed as much...
That could mean any number of things.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Reaction on player acquiring the ring. Might be from persuasion or from buying it from Omeluum.
EditorData.NodeContext: Suspicious of the mind flayer's words.

Text.Value: Use meditation to clear your mind.
Good to know. I have other priorities right now.
Very well. I abhor violence, and would rather prevent it where possible.
You would not survive the outcome. The tadpole must be completely crushed, and your skull along with it.
I greet you, sun child.
I'd like to learn more about the tadpole.
I changed my mind. What do you need to experiment on the tadpole?
So I went through all this and the tadpole's still lodged in my brain?
Swallow your disgust and permit the ghaik's search.
The southwest, when I last saw her. Although her tower does have a tendency... to move.
What shall you offer in exchange?
Resist the panic from within.
Your flesh has been burrowed into. Your flesh has been excavated. A tadpole need not tunnel when they greet their host.
Damn it all, why can't I remember?
Open your mind to me, friend. Let us see what lurks within.
A tincture distilled from a collection of rare mushrooms. They have subtle psionic influence.
*The parasite in your mind quiets, pleased with itself.*
I will not reward your hostility. Begone!
Where does this Lenore live?
*The acidic liquid tightens your throat, burning on the way down. It's a bolt of agony straight to your stomach.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Character winces and flinches in disgust, looking pained.

Text.Value: It will lower the psionic defences around the larva. If I cannot remove it, I may still be able to tell you more about its origin.
Can you extract the tadpole?
If you wish to acquire the ring later, you need only ask.
*It surges and twists, lashing out against that which would dare to intrude.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Camera focuses on Omeluum. The glowing effect lashes out at it.

Text.Value: The occupant was obsessed with magical plants. Sussur bark and the like. But no matter their source, I will take the mushrooms.
Leave.
How do you survive? Your kind must feast on sentient minds.
So, are the tales of slavering, brain-lusting mind flayers exaggerated?
How do you survive? Don't you need... brains?
Never mind. I'm not in the mood for sharing.
Yet that power may grow beyond your control. I have another intermediate solution, if you are in need.
How could a ghaik ever leave its colony?
You've certainly got a lot more individual ambition than your kin. Why is that?
How did you escape your colony?
What a brilliant experience. To feel one step closer to my ancestors is a fine gift indeed.
*Drawing on a lifetime of practice, you centre yourself. Your body is an anchor, implacable and calm.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player closes their eyes, physically relaxing.

Text.Value: Your conflict is with one I have never met. This ring protects me. I cannot surrender it for free.
Draw on your willpower and resist.
May your travels be safe and swift.
In nature, of course. But I imagine the nearby cleric's tower may also grow them.
Ah!
I thought it was always agonising, Omeluum.
Hm. I imagine Lenore would have them in her possession. She served Mystra as a cleric.
Well, yes, but that wasn't my point.
That potion of yours could have killed me. The tadpole almost did the same.
I can only theorise, but I suspect your transformation would be both agonising and instantaneous.
A pretty thing. And at least it offers us some protection from the tadpole.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Reaction on player acquiring the ring. Might be from persuasion or from buying it from Omeluum.
EditorData.NodeContext: stress on 'some' - you'd prefer more protection.

Text.Value: *Fear pierces your mind like knives of ice. The parasite digs deeper, as if it means to hollow out your skull.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player grabs their head in agony, tadpole halo FX/effect in place.

Text.Value: No. It appears to be shielded from physical and magical influence.
Leave.
Moreover, the cranium has undergone severe trauma. It is a miracle the brain functions at all. Extraction would risk much.
And even without the shield, the extraction would involve severe cranial trauma.
All that probing was useless in the end.
And I must admit, I was curious to study the tadpole myself.
May it serve you as well as it has served me.
That... is true. And I cannot imagine many other mind flayers will offer restitution.
The design was lost when the gith rebelled and ended our dominion.
Here. It is yours.
Timmasks cause confusion in those that approach them. The tongue is... self-explanatory.
Focus on the present, not the illusions.
Unfortunately, beyond the assessment of my own kind, I cannot speculate what has passed through your cerebrum.
How severe? I have healing magic.
How severe? I have healing magic.
Why would a cleric have a bunch of dangerous mushrooms?
Isn't the stasis why the tadpole hasn't killed me yet?
*Omeluum turns away to prepare the potion, lost in its own musings.*

Synopsis: Omeluum is a friendly, neutral mind flayer and member of the Society of Brilliance, dedicated to improving life in the Underdark. If attacked, it will teleport away rather than engaging in combat.
